OL,3,CFirst weekend of Makerfield by-
OL,4,Celection campaigns to get under way
OL,6,FHis campaign appears to have the
OL,7,Fbacking of several Labour figures who
OL,8,Fhave criticised Sir Keir.
OL,10,FMainstream, a Labour pressure group,
OL,11,Fhas announced plans for former first
OL,12,Fminister of Wales Mark Drakeford to
OL,13,Fjoin the campaign trail in early June.
OL,15,FMr Drakeford told Channel 4 News
OL,16,Fearlier this week that Sir Keir's
OL,17,Fpremiership "hasn't worked out ` it's
OL,18,Ftime to recognise that and make a plan
OL,19,Fto move ahead".
OL,26,@yD@MOU{D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1779584596
OL,3,CFirst weekend of Makerfield by-
OL,4,Celection campaigns to get under way
OL,6,FAlso listed are Simon Opher, the
OL,7,FStroud MP who has called for an
OL,8,F"orderly transition that brings
OL,9,Ftogether the very best talents across
OL,10,Fthe Labour Party", and Liverpool
OL,11,FWavertree MP Paula Barker, who
OL,12,Fpreviously told the BBC: "Andy would
OL,13,Fbe the person that I would like to see
OL,14,Flead our party."
OL,16,FMr Burnham faces Reform UK's Robert
OL,17,FKenyon in the by-election, a plumber
OL,18,Fwho said he is "ready to take on the
OL,19,FKing of the North" in a reference to
OL,20,FMr Burnham's moniker.
OL,26,@pD@AOUrD@QO]tD@ZOUvD@PO]zD@POU{D@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
